<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-357-436  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 357 436.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering  June 1989 v15 n6p760(11).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Algorithms for constructing minimal deduction graphs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yang, Chao-Chih; Chen, Jennifer Jau-Yin; Chau, H. Lewis.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Two efficient algorithms are developed for constructing minimaldeduction graphs (MDGs) for the solution of the rule inference andfact inference problems in rule-based expert systems based on HornClaus (HC) logic.andP;  Each MDG algorithm is based on a set ofreflexivity, transitivity, and conjunction rules for Horn formulae(HF) extensions of HCs.andP;  The MDG rule inference algorithm performsa rule inference without resort to recursive rules.andP;  The MDG factinference algorithm performs a fact inference, generates an AND-ORgraphical model of an HF from a program containing recursiverules, and checks the recursive rules for redundancy of extraneouspredicates.andP;  Development, validation and application of thealgorithms are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Knowledge-Based SystemsAlgorithmsExpert SystemsRule-Based SystemsProgramming.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartprogram.andO;Caption:   Graphical representation of HF's and a rule. (chart)Main program and procedures. (program)A tree for constructing mdg. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>